# Project Conventions

## Stack
- Next.js 16 App Router + TypeScript 5 + Tailwind CSS 4
- React 19 client components use `"use client"` directive
- All shared TypeScript types live in `src/types/`

## Language & Locale
- UI text is in **Portuguese (pt-BR)**
- All number, currency and percentage formatting uses `pt-BR` locale:

```typescript
// ✅ Currency
value.toLocaleString("pt-BR", { style: "currency", currency: "BRL" })

// ✅ Percentage
`${value >= 0 ? "+" : ""}${value.toFixed(2)}%`
```

## Design System
- Background: `bg-gray-950` (page) / `bg-gray-900` (cards)
- Accent / positive: `text-emerald-400`, `bg-emerald-500`
- Negative / error: `text-red-400`, `bg-red-900/40 border-red-700`
- Text hierarchy: `text-white` → `text-gray-400` → `text-gray-500`
- Borders: `border-gray-800` / `border-gray-700`

## Environment Variables
- `BRAPI_TOKEN` in `.env.local` — never expose to the client, read only in API Routes
- `.env.local` is gitignored by default — never commit it
